notesStmt.note: 620 leaves foliated 1-620, upper left and lower right verso.

Mistakes blacked out; corrections and additions in margins; some significant syllables, words, or phrases highlighted in red; vertical margins marked with quadruple red line. Text was written by two or more scribal hands.
Watermark of an emblematic design featuring the letters GB in the center.
A single wooden board wrapped in manuscript paper supports the manuscript.

msIdentifier.repository: Kislak Center for Special Collections, Rare Books and Manuscripts

msContents.summary: Philosophical treatise and commentary on Jaiminīya's Mīmāṃsāsūtra, from the perspective of Pūrva Mīmāṃsa, a branch of Vedānta philosophy.
